Description: Fix CVE-2026-3039 GSS-API resource leak in TKEY/GSS-API error paths
 BIND 9 servers configured to use TKEY-based authentication via GSS-API
 tokens are vulnerable to excessive memory consumption when receiving and
 processing maliciously-constructed packets. On error paths,
 dst_gssapi_acceptctx() failed to release the allocated output token
 buffer and the GSS-API security context, and process_gsstkey() returned
 early after dst_gssapi_acceptctx() failure (or when the negotiated
 context had an empty principal) without freeing the GSS-API context
 and output token. An unauthenticated attacker could exhaust server
 memory by sending repeated TKEY queries to a server with
 tkey-gssapi-keytab or tkey-gssapi-credential configured.
 .
 This patch backports upstream commit 11276087 ("Fix output token and
 GSS context leaks in TKEY/GSS-API error paths") to BIND 9.16.50.
 Adapted for 9.16: cleanup label is named "out:" (not "cleanup:"), the
 RETERR macro is used (not CHECK), and the GSSAPI preprocessor guard
 is "#ifdef GSSAPI" (not "#if HAVE_GSSAPI").
Origin: backport, https://gitlab.isc.org/isc-projects/bind9/-/commit/11276087a74f0c79885524ea913fcee3d759324e
Bug: https://gitlab.isc.org/isc-projects/bind9/-/issues/5752
Author: Ondrej Sury <ondrej@isc.org>
Last-Update: 2026-06-09

